Objective Evidence of Brain Injury Can be Quantified

Request Demo

Symptom-Based Mapping of Brain Health Using Advanced Quantitative Analysis

Quantify® delivers precise, reliable brain analysis using advanced MRI techniques and comparisons against a large, scientifically-validated database of healthy controls. Our solution ensures accurate results through calibrated scanners and rigorous quality control, providing objective findings that, when present, can be related to known functional correlations in the brain.

Our Capabilities
We translate the complexities of brain health and expert analysis into practical, reliable data with scientific credibility.

Volumetric Analysis

Precise grey matter measurements identify regional abnormalities based on a functional atlas that correlates with neuropsychological testing.

DTI Analysis

White matter integrity evaluation across 48 major tracts, where the brain’s white matter is most susceptible to trauma.

Scanner Harmonization

MINDSET’s unique scaling process calibrates every scanner to the database, ensuring consistency and accuracy across the analyses

Normative Databse

The MINDSET database contains more than 1,000 healthy control subjects, all collected and harmonized to account for scanner noise. 

False Positive Mitigation

Determinations of abnormalities are rigorously evaluated to account for false positives related to multiple comparisons, for increased reliability.

Expert Functional Assessment

Expert interpretation of abnormal findings by qualified experts to assess their potential impact on cognitive function and daily life

Scientific Rigor

Designed with sensitivity and reliability in mind, Quantify undergoes rigorous scientific evaluation to ensure the highest quality of analysis and findings

Admissibility Support

MINDSET has successfully supported the admissibility of its quantitative volumetric and DTI analysis for more than a decade.

Revolutionizing Brain Analysis
Experience the power of Quantify's cutting-edge technology, delivering precise brain analysis through advanced imaging, accurate data processing, and a scientifically-validated control database.
Data Collection & Calibration​
  • Collecting high-resolution MRI data that captures detailed brain measurements.
  • Millimeter-thin image slices ensure no detail is missed.
  • Scaling scanners to the MINDSET database for consistent accuracy.
Advanced Analysis​
  • Organizing volumetric gray matter into 101 brain regions and measuring white matter integrity across 48 tracts.
  • Comparing white matter Fractional Anisotropy (FA) and gray matter values with a control group more than 1,000 subjects.
  • Applying statistical corrections to ensure reliable results.
Quality Control​
  • Conducting automatic screening for noise and artifacts prior to analysis.
  • Having all findings reviewed and validated by neuroscientists.
Objective Evaluation​
  • Providing objective evaluation of DTI and gray matter data, the gold standard in brain studies.
  • Offering comprehensive insights into brain abnormalities.
